# Allowed Packages and Usage Guidelines

## Core Framework & Runtime

- **next**: React framework for production - use for server-side rendering, static generation, and API routes
- **react**: UI library - use for building component-based user interfaces
- **react-dom**: React rendering for web - use for DOM manipulation and hydration

## Database & ORM

- **@prisma/client**: Type-safe database client - use for database queries with full TypeScript support
- **prisma**: Database toolkit - use for schema management, migrations, and database introspection

## Authentication & Security

- **@node-rs/argon2**: Fast Argon2 password hashing - use for secure password storage and verification
- **@oslojs/crypto**: Cryptographic utilities - use for secure random generation and encryption
- **@oslojs/encoding**: Encoding utilities - use for base64, hex, and other encoding operations
- **@zxcvbn-ts/core**: Password strength estimation - use for real-time password strength feedback
- **zxcvbn**: Password strength library - use for comprehensive password analysis

## UI Components & Styling

- **@radix-ui/react-alert-dialog**: Accessible alert dialogs - use for confirmation modals and destructive actions
- **@radix-ui/react-avatar**: Accessible avatar component - use for user profile pictures and initials
- **@radix-ui/react-dropdown-menu**: Accessible dropdown menus - use for navigation and action menus
- **@radix-ui/react-label**: Accessible form labels - use for form field labeling with proper accessibility
- **@radix-ui/react-popover**: Accessible popover component - use for contextual information and tooltips
- **@radix-ui/react-select**: Accessible select component - use for dropdown selection with keyboard navigation
- **@radix-ui/react-separator**: Accessible separator component - use for visual dividers and section breaks
- **@radix-ui/react-slot**: Component slot utility - use for component composition and prop forwarding
- **@radix-ui/react-tabs**: Accessible tabs component - use for tabbed interfaces and navigation
- **class-variance-authority**: Component variant management - use for creating flexible component APIs
- **clsx**: Conditional className utility - use for dynamic CSS class composition
- **tailwind-merge**: Tailwind class merging - use for combining Tailwind classes without conflicts
- **tailwindcss-animate**: Tailwind animations - use for smooth transitions and micro-interactions

## State Management & Data Fetching

- **@tanstack/react-query**: Server state management - use for caching, synchronization, and background updates
- **@tanstack/react-query-devtools**: React Query dev tools - use for debugging and monitoring queries

## Form Handling & Validation

- **zod**: TypeScript-first schema validation - use for runtime type checking and form validation

## Date & Time

- **date-fns**: Date utility library - use for date manipulation, formatting, and calculations
- **react-day-picker**: Date picker component - use for date selection in forms

## Email & Communication

- **@react-email/components**: Email template components - use for building transactional email templates
- **resend**: Email delivery service - use for sending transactional emails

## Background Jobs & Scheduling

- **inngest**: Background job processing - use for handling async tasks and scheduled operations

## UI Utilities & Interactions

- **lucide-react**: Icon library - use for consistent iconography throughout the app
- **react-intersection-observer**: Intersection observer hook - use for lazy loading and scroll-based animations
- **sonner**: Toast notifications - use for user feedback and system messages

## URL & Search Management

- **nuqs**: URL search params management - use for syncing state with URL parameters

## Mathematical Operations

- **big.js**: Decimal arithmetic library - use for precise financial calculations and currency handling
- **@types/big.js**: TypeScript types for big.js

## String & Text Processing

- **fastest-levenshtein**: Fast string similarity - use for fuzzy search and text matching

## Theme Management

- **next-themes**: Theme switching - use for dark/light mode support

## Performance & Optimization

- **use-debounce**: Debounced values hook - use for search inputs and expensive operations

## Development Tools

- **@types/node**: Node.js TypeScript types
- **@types/react**: React TypeScript types
- **@types/react-dom**: React DOM TypeScript types
- **@types/zxcvbn**: Zxcvbn TypeScript types
- **eslint**: Code linting - use for maintaining code quality and consistency
- **eslint-config-next**: Next.js ESLint configuration
- **eslint-plugin-simple-import-sort**: Import sorting - use for consistent import organization
- **prettier**: Code formatting - use for consistent code style
- **prettier-plugin-tailwindcss**: Tailwind class sorting - use for organized Tailwind classes
- **react-email**: Email development - use for previewing email templates locally
- **tailwindcss**: Utility-first CSS framework - use for rapid UI development
- **tsx**: TypeScript execution - use for running TypeScript files directly
- **tw-animate-css**: Tailwind animation utilities - use for additional animation classes
- **typescript**: TypeScript compiler - use for type checking and compilation

## Build & Development

- **@eslint/eslintrc**: ESLint configuration utilities
- **@tailwindcss/postcss**: Tailwind PostCSS plugin
- **@types/big.js**: TypeScript definitions for big.js

## Package Management

- **package-lock.json**: Locked dependency versions for reproducible builds
- **overrides**: Package version overrides for dependency resolution

## Usage Guidelines

- Prefer existing packages over adding new dependencies
- Use TypeScript-first solutions when available
- Prioritize accessibility and performance
- Follow the principle of least privilege for security packages
- Use development dependencies only for build-time tools
- Maintain consistent versioning across related packages
